    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "here it is:\n\n4.2 Price Adjustments: The Supplier reserves the right to implement a price adjustment of up to 5% on the base rate during peak seasonal months (defined as June, July, and August) to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be enacted automatically at the commencement of the specified month. All other modifications to the pricing structure require a mutual written amendment signed by both parties.\n\nDoes this mean they can just change the price on us during the summer without asking?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
